and Ahmed a microcosm of a wider
narrative.

23:33.045 --> 23:39.318 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Naor comes from Pisgat Ze'ev, a
Jewish settlement in Eastern
Jerusalem. It is built on land

23:39.318 --> 23:45.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
captured by Israel in 1967, and
is considered illegal under
international law. Israel
disputes

23:45.391 --> 23:47.726 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

23:47.726 --> 23:53.599 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ahmed comes from the Palestinian
village of Beit Hanina. Pisgat
Ze'ev and Beit Hanina

23:53.599 --> 24:00.472 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are separated by a highway, but
there is an enormous cultural
and religious divide. Jews

24:00.472 --> 24:04.810 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
